  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "16. John answered—either to the deputation from Jerusalem (see Joh 1:19, &c.), or on some other occasion, simply to remove impressions derogatory to his blessed Master which he knew to be taking hold of the popular mind. (Also see on [1556]Mt 3:10.)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "saying unto them all—in solemn protestation. So far from entertaining such a thought as laying claim to the honors of Messiahship, the meanest services I can render to that \"Mightier than I that is coming after me,\" are too high an honor for me. Beautiful spirit, distinguishing this servant of Christ throughout!",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "one mightier than I—\"the Mighter than I.\"",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
